ased perspective. The book argues that without adequate research and appropriate management of educational forms of tourism, the potential regional development impacts and personal learning benefits will not be maximised. The book highlights the need for collaboration and networking between both the tourism and education industries to adequately manage the issues surrounding the growth in educational tourism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aForeign study. 0aStudentsxTravel. 0aTourism. 0aTourisme éducatif. 0aÉlèvesxVoyages. 0aÉtudes à l'étranger. 0aÉtudiantsxVoyages. 4aEDUCATION. 4aTourism industry. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  acultural heritage tourism.  aecotourism.  aeducational holidays.  aeducational tourism.  aeducational travel.  alanguage learning.  alifelong learning.  aoffshore education.  astudent exchanges.1 aCarr, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRitchie, B. W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCVP eBook-Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311075437740uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978187315052840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781873150528423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781873150528.jpg  a978-3-11-075437-7  CVP eBook-Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK